endpoint_memberships/service-card.addCar.description: This endpoint allows you to add an additional card for an existing member under a specific membership. It is useful when a member needs a new card for identification or for cases where multiple cards are allowed for the same member (e.g., secondary or replacement cards).

endpoint_memberships/service-card.replac.description: Use this endpoint to replace an existing member card with a new one. When a card is replaced, the old card is blocked, and a new card is issued to the member. This is typically used when a card is lost, damaged, or needs to be reissued.

endpoint_memberships/service-card.getCar.description: Retrieve details about a specific card using its unique card ID. This endpoint provides detailed information about the card, such as the member it belongs to, its status, and its validity.

Retrieve details of a specific card using its card number. This endpoint allows access to card information when the card number is known, providing key details such as the card's status and associated member.

endpoint_memberships/service-card.regist.description: This endpoint registers the member's arrival at a facility using their card. The card number is used to log the arrival and generate a ticket for the member. Use Ticketing API to retrieve ticket details using the ticket number.

endpoint_memberships/service-card.sendTo.description: Sends the card to the apple wallet via email or phone number specified in the request.

endpoint_memberships/service-catalog.get.description: Get the list of membership items and their descriptions for a specific store.

examples.name: ExampleCatalog1
examples.description: Example response for the getCatalog endpoint

endpoint_memberships/service-lifecycle.g.description: Use this endpoint to retrieve the lifecycle history of a membership. It provides a chronological log of events, including creation, renewals, upgrades, and cancellations.

endpoint_memberships/service-lifecycle.a.description: Activate a membership that has been created but is not yet active. This is commonly used when a membership is set up ahead of time and needs to be activated for use.

endpoint_memberships/service-lifecycle.c.description: Cancel an active membership using this endpoint. You can provide a cancellation date, allowing the membership to run until that date, or cancel it immediately.

endpoint_memberships/service-lifecycle.g.description: Retrieve a list of available renewal options for a membership. Each option is represented by an `itemNumber`, which includes predefined configurations such as price, duration, and other relevant details. The `itemNumber` returned from this endpoint can be used as a parameter in the `renewMembership` endpoint to proceed with the renewal.

endpoint_memberships/service-lifecycle.r.description: Use this endpoint to renew an existing membership. The renewal will **add a new period** after the current membership period expires. To renew, you must provide the `itemNumber` from the `getRenewalOptions` endpoint, which specifies the predefined renewal configuration such as price and duration.

endpoint_memberships/service-lifecycle.g.description: Retrieve a list of available upgrade options for a membership. Each upgrade option is represented by an `itemNumber`, which includes predefined details such as the upgraded benefits and any pricing adjustments. The `itemNumber` returned from this endpoint can be used as a parameter in the `upgradeMembership` endpoint to execute the upgrade.

renewalOptions.description: Upgrade to PLATINUM Membership for the remaining period

endpoint_memberships/service-lifecycle.u.description: Use this endpoint to upgrade an active membership to a higher (or lower) plan or tier. The upgrade will **terminate the current membership period** and apply the new membership tier immediately. However, the **overall membership duration remains unchanged**. You must provide the `itemNumber` from the `getUpgradeOptions` endpoint, which includes the predefined details for the upgrade.

endpoint_memberships/service-lifecycle.g.description: Retrieve a list of available extension options for a membership. Each option is represented by an `itemNumber`, which includes predefined configurations such as new duration and pricing. The `itemNumber` returned from this endpoint can be used as a parameter in the `extendMembership` endpoint to apply the extension.

extendOptions.description: Extend GOLD Membership with 1 year from today

endpoint_memberships/service-lifecycle.e.description: Use this endpoint to extend the duration of an active membership. The extension will **terminate the current period** and create a **new period starting from today**, based on the provided extension configuration. The **overall membership duration will be greater** than the original duration. You must provide the `itemNumber` from the `getExtendOptions` endpoint to apply the extension.

endpoint_memberships/service-member.addM.description: Use this endpoint to add a new member to a membership. This is used when a new individual needs to be linked to an existing membership, either at the time of membership creation or later.

curl.code:
curl -X POST https://api.npretail.app/01234567-89ab-cdef-0123-456789abcdef/production/CRONUS%20International%20Ltd./memberships/member/1224/add \
     -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
     -d '{
  "membershipId": 1224,
  "member": {
    "address": "123 Main Street",
    "birthday": "1980-01-01",
    "cards": [
      {
        "cardNumber": "MC1234567890",
        "expiryDate": "2029-09-17",
        "temporary": false
      }
    ],
    "city": "New York",
    "country": "USA",
    "email": "john.doe@acme.com",
    "firstName": "John",
    "gender": "male",
    "lastName": "Doe",
    "middleName": "A.",
    "newsletter": true,
    "phoneNo": "+1234567890",
    "postCode": "12345"
  }
}'

endpoint_memberships/service-member.getM.description: Retrieve details of a specific member using their unique member ID.
Use this endpoint to retrieve details of a member based on their member number. This is helpful when the member number is available but the member ID is not known.

endpoint_memberships/service-member.bloc.description: Block a specific member from further activity. This is typically used in scenarios where a member's access needs to be temporarily or permanently disabled. **Family Membership Downgrade** For family or group memberships, when the allowed number of valid members decreases (e.g., before a downgrade to a smaller membership plan), this endpoint can be used to block excess members to comply with the new membership limitations.

endpoint_memberships/service-member.unbl.description: Unblock a previously blocked member, allowing them to resume activities associated with their membership. This endpoint re-enables access that was previously restricted.

endpoint_memberships/service-member.upda.description: Update the details of an existing member. This endpoint is used when a member's information needs to be changed, such as updating their contact details, name, or personal information.

curl.code:
curl -X PUT https://api.npretail.app/01234567-89ab-cdef-0123-456789abcdef/production/CRONUS%20International%20Ltd./memberships/member/4331 \
     -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
     -d '{
  "member": {
    "firstName": "John",
    "middleName": "A.",
    "lastName": "Doe",
    "address": "123 Main Street",
    "postCode": "12345",
    "city": "New York",
    "country": "USA",
    "birthday": "1980-01-01",
    "gender": "male",
    "newsletter": true,
    "phoneNo": "+1234567890",
    "email": "john.doe@acme.com"
  }
}'

endpoint_memberships/service-member.getM.description: Retrieve the image associated with a specific member.

endpoint_memberships/service-member.setM.description: Create or update the image associated with a member. Use this endpoint to upload a new photo or update an existing one linked to the members profile.

endpoint_memberships/service-member.find.description: Search for members based on various criteria such as name, birth date, email, phone number, or card number. This endpoint allows you to perform a flexible search and return a list of members that match the provided criteria.

curl.code:
curl -G https://api.npretail.app/01234567-89ab-cdef-0123-456789abcdef/production/CRONUS%20International%20Ltd./memberships/member \
     -d memberNumber=M123456789 \
     -d lastName=Doe \
     -d birthDate=1980-01-01 \
     --data-urlencode email=john.doe@acme.com \
     --data-urlencode phone=+1234567890 \
     -d cardNumber=MC1234567890

This endpoint replaces the current reservation details with new ones provided in the request, such as changing quantities or items. Useful for adjusting reservations before confirmation, ensuring that held tickets are updated and previous allocations are released.

endpoint_ticketing/service-reservations..description: Cancels an existing registered reservation using its token. This endpoint releases the held tickets back into the system, making them available for other customers. Note that confirmed reservations cannot be canceled using this endpoint; they must be revoked through a different process.

Extends the lifespan of a provisional reservation identified by a token. Clients use this endpoint to keep the reservation active for a longer period before confirming it, preventing the tickets from expiring and being released back into the system. This action is typically taken when you want to extend the reservation's lifespan just before starting the payment process.

Finalizes a provisional reservation, turning it into a confirmed booking. This endpoint requires the reservation token and may include additional customer information such as ticket holder details and payment reference. Upon successful confirmation, the reservation status is updated, and ticket numbers are assigned.

endpoint_ticketing/service-ticket.revoke.description: Revokes a ticket identified by its ticketNumber, effectively canceling it after it has been confirmed. This action makes the ticket invalid for entry or use and releases any held resources. Useful for handling refunds or cancellations initiated by the customer or the system.

endpoint_ticketing/service-ticket.valida.description: Validates a ticket for arrival at a specific admission point, marking the ticket as admitted. This endpoint is typically used at entry points (e.g., gates or doors) to verify the ticket's validity and record the customer's arrival. Optional parameters like admissionCode and scannerStation provide context for the validation.

Validates a ticket for departure from an admission, marking the ticket as departed. Used when tracking both entry and exit of customers, this endpoint helps manage capacities and ensures that the ticket is correctly processed upon leaving. Similar to arrival validation, it can include admissionCode and scannerStation.

Validates the arrival of a member using their member card number, possibly creating a reservation on-the-fly if necessary. This endpoint is used when members, such as season pass holders or VIPs, arrive at an admission point without a prior reservation. It ensures that their access is recorded and any tickets are generated accordingly.

This endpoint facilitates electronic delivery of tickets, allowing customers to receive and present their tickets digitally. Useful for post-purchase communications and ensuring customers have access to their tickets.

endpoint_ticketing/service-ticket.exchan.description: Exchanges a ticket for a coupon, which can be used for discounts on future purchases. This endpoint is used when a customer opts to convert their ticket into a coupon, providing multiple value retention options. The ticket is validated, and a coupon is issued, providing value retention for the customer.

type_memberships/types/types-simple:Birt.description: The birth date of the member.

type_memberships/types/types-simple:News.name: Newsletter
type_memberships/types/types-simple:News.description: Indicates whether the member is subscribed to the newsletter.

type_memberships/types/types-simple:Phon.name: PhoneNo
type_memberships/types/types-simple:Phon.description: The phone number of the member.

type_memberships/types/types-simple:Emai.name: Email
type_memberships/types/types-simple:Emai.description: The email address of the member.

type_memberships/types/types-simple:Base.name: Base64Image
type_memberships/types/types-simple:Base.description: Base64 encoded image of the member.

type_memberships/types/types-simple:GDPR.name: GDPRApproval
type_memberships/types/types-simple:GDPR.description: Indicates if the member has given GDPR approval.

type_memberships/types/types-simple:Noti.name: NotificationMethod
type_memberships/types/types-simple:Noti.description: The preferred notification method for the member.

type_memberships/types/types-simple:Noti.name: NotificationAddress
type_memberships/types/types-simple:Noti.description: The email address or mobile phone number to send cards and notifications to

type_memberships/types/types-simple:Expi.name: ExpiryDate
type_memberships/types/types-simple:Expi.description: The expiry date of the card.

type_memberships/types/types-simple:Temp.name: TemporaryCard
type_memberships/types/types-simple:Temp.description: Indicates whether the card is temporary.

type_memberships/types/types-simple:Docu.name: DocumentId
type_memberships/types/types-simple:Docu.description: Unique identifier for the membership document.

type_memberships/types/types-simple:Crea.name: CreatedAt
type_memberships/types/types-simple:Crea.description: Date and time when the membership period was created.

type_memberships/types/types-simple:Cont.name: Context
type_memberships/types/types-simple:Cont.description: Context name associated with the membership period.

type_memberships/types/types-simple:Bloc.name: Blocked
type_memberships/types/types-simple:Bloc.description: Indicates whether the membership period is blocked.

type_memberships/types/types-simple:Acti.name: Active
type_memberships/types/types-simple:Acti.description: Indicates whether the membership period is active.

type_memberships/types/types-simple:Acti.name: ActivateOnFirstUse
type_memberships/types/types-simple:Acti.description: Specifies if the membership will activate upon first use.

type_memberships/types/types-simple:Prod.name: ProductId
type_memberships/types/types-simple:Prod.description: Identifier for the product associated with the membership period.

type_memberships/types/types-simple:Loya.name: LoyaltyProgram
type_memberships/types/types-simple:Loya.description: Name of the loyalty program associated with the membership.

type_memberships/types/types-simple:Memb.name: MemberCardinality
type_memberships/types/types-simple:Memb.description: Cardinality of the member in the membership.

type_memberships/types/types-simple:Fiel.name: FieldEntryNo
type_memberships/types/types-simple:Fiel.description: Number representing the specific field id to update.

type_memberships/types/types-simple:Limi.name: Limit
type_memberships/types/types-simple:Limi.description: The maximum number of results to return.

type_memberships/types/types-simple:Offs.name: Offset
type_memberships/types/types-simple:Offs.description: The starting point for results, used for pagination.

type_memberships/types/types-simple:Stor.name: StoreCode
type_memberships/types/types-simple:Stor.description: A unique identifier for a store - a logical grouping defining a subset of membership items. This is used to filter the list of membership related items returned by the API.

type_ticketing/service-capacity:Admissio.name: AdmissionCapacity
type_ticketing/service-capacity:Admissio.description: Provides detailed capacity and availability information for a specific admission associated with a ticket item. Includes pricing, quantity, and schedule details to help determine if the desired number of tickets can be reserved on a particular date.

type_ticketing/service-capacity:Admissio.name: AdmissionSearch
type_ticketing/service-capacity:Admissio.description: Represents the criteria used to search for capacity information for an admission. Used in requests to specify the ticket item, date, quantity, and optionally filter by admission code or customer number.

type_ticketing/service-capacity:Schedule.name: Schedule
type_ticketing/service-capacity:Schedule.description: Contains information about a specific schedule or time slot for an admission, including whether it can be allocated (reserved), remaining capacity, pricing adjustments, and sales periods. Helps clients identify available schedules and understand any limitations or special pricing.

type_ticketing/service-capacity:Schedule.name: SchedulePrice
type_ticketing/service-capacity:Schedule.description: Details pricing adjustments applied to an admission's base price for a specific schedule. Includes information on dynamic pricing options, adjustment amounts or percentages, and calculates the adjusted unit and total prices for the reservation.

type_ticketing/service-capacity:Schedule.name: ScheduleSales
type_ticketing/service-capacity:Schedule.description: Specifies the sales period for a schedule, indicating when ticket sales start and end for that schedule. Informs clients about the booking window, enabling them to display availability and enforce booking rules accordingly.

type_ticketing/service-catalog:StoreCata.name: StoreCatalogResponse
type_ticketing/service-catalog:StoreCata.description: Represents the catalog of ticket items available at a specific store. Includes the store code and a list of items that customers can browse and purchase.

type_ticketing/service-catalog:Item.name: Item
type_ticketing/service-catalog:Item.description: Describes a ticket item available for sale, including its unique identifier, pricing, type, descriptions, and associated admissions. Used to present detailed ticket options to customers.

type_ticketing/service-catalog:ItemVaria.name: ItemVariant
type_ticketing/service-catalog:ItemVaria.description: Additional details for an item number. If the item number is a variant, this will contain the variant code, description and the specific item number for that combination .

type_ticketing/service-catalog:Recommend.name: RecommendedPrice
type_ticketing/service-catalog:Recommend.description: Suggests a base price for a ticket item before any adjustments like discounts or dynamic pricing. Assists in displaying price information to customers during their purchasing decision.

type_ticketing/service-catalog:TicketTyp.name: TicketType
type_ticketing/service-catalog:TicketTyp.description: Categorizes the ticket item based on sales channels or functional groupings, such as "WEB" or "POS". Influences how the ticket is sold and processed within the system.

type_ticketing/service-catalog:Admission.name: AdmissionCatalog
type_ticketing/service-catalog:Admission.description: Details the admissions included with a ticket item, specifying access rights like entry to events or exhibits. Informs customers about what experiences are included with their purchase.

type_ticketing/service-reservations:Crea.name: CreateReservationRequest
type_ticketing/service-reservations:Crea.description: Used when initiating a new reservation for tickets. Contains a list of items (reserve) that the customer wants to reserve, specifying the ticket item numbers, quantities, and any additional content like admissions and schedules.

type_ticketing/service-reservations:Conf.name: ConfirmReservationRequest
type_ticketing/service-reservations:Conf.description: Submitted when confirming a reservation, finalizing the ticket purchase. May include customer details such as ticketHolder name, notificationAddress for sending tickets or notifications, and a paymentReference to link the reservation to a payment transaction.

type_ticketing/service-reservations:Crea.name: CreateReservationItemRequest
type_ticketing/service-reservations:Crea.description: Represents an individual ticket item within a reservation request. Includes the itemNumber, the desired quantity of tickets, and optional content detailing specific admissions or schedules associated with the ticket.

type_ticketing/service-reservations:GetR.name: GetReservationDetails
type_ticketing/service-reservations:GetR.description: Returned in response to reservation-related operations to provide the current state of the reservation. Includes the token identifying the reservation, its expiresAt timestamp, reservationStatus, and a list of reserved items (reservations) with their details.

type_ticketing/service-reservations:Rese.name: ReservationActionResponse
type_ticketing/service-reservations:Rese.description: Provides a simplified response after performing actions like canceling or pre-confirming a reservation. Includes the updated reservationStatus and optionally the new expiresAt time if the reservation's lifespan was extended.

type_ticketing/service-reservations:Rese.name: ReservationItemDetails
type_ticketing/service-reservations:Rese.description: Contains detailed information about a specific item in a reservation. Includes the itemNumber, quantity reserved, associated ticket details, and a list of content items specifying admissions or other components included with the ticket.

type_ticketing/service-reservations:Tick.name: TicketContentDetails
type_ticketing/service-reservations:Tick.description: Provides details about the admissions or content associated with a reserved ticket item. Contains admissionDetails that specify the particular admissions, schedules, and any relevant information for each component of the ticket.

type_ticketing/service-reservations:Admi.name: AdmissionDetailsFull
type_ticketing/service-reservations:Admi.description: Extends AdmissionDetails with additional information specific to reservations, such as the reschedulePolicy. Offers comprehensive details about an admission, including policies affecting changes after reservation.

type_ticketing/service-reservations:Rese.name: ReservationTicketDetails
type_ticketing/service-reservations:Rese.description: Offers detailed ticket information within a reservation, including ticketNumbers if confirmed, validity periods (validFrom, validUntil), pricing details, and optional customer information like pinCode and ticketHolder name. Used to inform customers about their tickets and any actions they can perform.

type_ticketing/service-ticket:SendTicket.name: SendTicketRequest
type_ticketing/service-ticket:SendTicket.description: Request to send a ticket as an e-ticket

type_ticketing/service-ticket:CreateMemb.name: CreateMemberReservationRequest
type_ticketing/service-ticket:CreateMemb.description: Request to validate a member arrival

type_ticketing/service-ticket:GetTicketC.name: GetTicketCouponRequest
type_ticketing/service-ticket:GetTicketC.description: Request to exchange a ticket for a coupon

type_ticketing/service-ticket:ActionResp.name: ActionResponseSuccess
type_ticketing/service-ticket:ActionResp.description: Indicates whether the action was successful

type_ticketing/service-ticket:ActionResp.name: ActionResponseCode
type_ticketing/service-ticket:ActionResp.description: A code that identifies the reason of the action result

type_ticketing/service-ticket:ActionResp.name: ActionResponseMessage
type_ticketing/service-ticket:ActionResp.description: A message that describes the result of the action

type_ticketing/types-composite:Admission.name: AdmissionBase
type_ticketing/types-composite:Admission.description: An admission component for a specific item number.

type_ticketing/types-composite:Admission.name: AdmissionDetails
type_ticketing/types-composite:Admission.description: Details of the admission for a specific reservation

type_ticketing/types-composite:ScheduleD.name: ScheduleDetails
type_ticketing/types-composite:ScheduleD.description: Details of the schedule for a specific time slot.

type_ticketing/types-composite:Descripti.name: Descriptions
type_ticketing/types-composite:Descripti.description: Descriptive information about a ticket item. The source of these fields are configurable.

type_ticketing/types-errors:ErrorCode.name: ErrorCode
type_ticketing/types-errors:ErrorCode.description: A unique identifier for an error

type_ticketing/types-simple:Token.name: Token
type_ticketing/types-simple:Token.description: A unique token that identifies a ticket reservation

type_ticketing/types-simple:ItemNumber.name: ItemNumber
type_ticketing/types-simple:ItemNumber.description: An item or product number defined in the ticketing system

type_ticketing/types-simple:AdmissionCod.name: AdmissionCode
type_ticketing/types-simple:AdmissionCod.description: A unique code that identifies a specific admission.

type_ticketing/types-simple:ScheduleId.name: ScheduleId
type_ticketing/types-simple:ScheduleId.description: The ID of a specific time slot for a specific admission

type_ticketing/types-simple:NumberOfTick.name: NumberOfTickets
type_ticketing/types-simple:NumberOfTick.description: The number of tickets to reserved

type_ticketing/types-simple:ExpiresAt.name: ExpiresAt
type_ticketing/types-simple:ExpiresAt.description: The date and time when the token expires and reservation is no longer valid

type_ticketing/types-simple:TicketHolder.name: TicketHolder
type_ticketing/types-simple:TicketHolder.description: The name of the person holding the ticket(s)

type_ticketing/types-simple:Notification.name: NotificationAddress
type_ticketing/types-simple:Notification.description: The email address or mobile phone number to send tickets and notifications to

type_ticketing/types-simple:PaymentRefer.name: PaymentReference
type_ticketing/types-simple:PaymentRefer.description: A reference to the payment transaction. Unless provided, the reservation is not considered paid. A confirmed unpaid reservation must be paid on site before the tickets are valid for usage.

type_ticketing/types-simple:TicketId.name: TicketId
type_ticketing/types-simple:TicketId.description: The unique identifier of a ticket

type_ticketing/types-simple:PinCode.name: PinCode
type_ticketing/types-simple:PinCode.description: A pin code for the ticket, used for validation when rescheduling or revoking a confirmed ticket

type_ticketing/types-simple:UnitPrice.name: UnitPrice
type_ticketing/types-simple:UnitPrice.description: The unit price of the ticket.

type_ticketing/types-simple:UnitPriceInc.name: UnitPriceIncludesVat
type_ticketing/types-simple:UnitPriceInc.description: Indicates if the unit price includes VAT.

type_ticketing/types-simple:DiscountPct.name: DiscountPct
type_ticketing/types-simple:DiscountPct.description: The discount percentage for the admission based either on the customer or the quantity of tickets.

type_ticketing/types-simple:VatPct.name: VatPct
type_ticketing/types-simple:VatPct.description: The VAT percentage for the admission.

type_ticketing/types-simple:StoreCode.name: StoreCode
type_ticketing/types-simple:StoreCode.description: A unique identifier for a store - a logical grouping defining a subset of ticket items. This is used to filter the list of ticket items returned by the API.

type_ticketing/types-simple:CustomerNumb.name: CustomerNumber
type_ticketing/types-simple:CustomerNumb.description: The customer number of the user making the request. The customer number affects pricing.

type_ticketing/types-simple:ReferenceDat.name: ReferenceDate
type_ticketing/types-simple:ReferenceDat.description: A date to use as a reference for the capacity search. If not specified, the current date will be used.

type_ticketing/types-simple:ReferenceDat.name: ReferenceDateTime
type_ticketing/types-simple:ReferenceDat.description: A date and time to use as a reference for the capacity search. If not specified, the current date and time will be used.

type_ticketing/types-simple:DefaultAdmis.name: DefaultAdmission
type_ticketing/types-simple:DefaultAdmis.description: Indicates if this admission is the default admission when there are multiple admission defined.

type_ticketing/types-simple:AdmissionIsI.name: AdmissionIsIncluded
type_ticketing/types-simple:AdmissionIsI.description: Indicates if the admission is mandatory or optional. Mandatory implies that the admission can not be deselected. Optional implies that you must opt-in to include the admission, while optionalSelected implies that the admission is optional but selected by default.

type_ticketing/types-simple:CapacityCont.name: CapacityControl
type_ticketing/types-simple:CapacityCont.description: Indicates the type of capacity control for the admission. None implies that there is no capacity control. Sales implies that the capacity is controlled by the number of tickets sold. Admitted implies that the capacity is controlled by the number of tickets admitted. Full implies that the capacity is admitted and departed.

type_ticketing/types-simple:ScheduleSele.name: ScheduleSelection
type_ticketing/types-simple:ScheduleSele.description: All reservations require a schedule id. However, this field indicates the type of automation you get when performing a reservation without providing schedule id for the admission. _ NoScheduleSelection implies that there is no *automatic* schedule selection when no schedule id provided (reservation will fail). _ CurrentSchedule implies that the current schedule (aka "today") is selected. \* NextAvailableSchedule implies that the next available schedule is selected. The current and Next-available select rules work well in a POS sales scenario.

type_ticketing/types-simple:PricingOptio.name: PricingOption
type_ticketing/types-simple:PricingOptio.description: The pricing option for the schedule. Fixed implies that the price is fixed - calculated by the ERP module only. Dynamic_fixed_amount implies that the price is fixed but set by the schedule rather than the ERP module. Dynamic_relative_amount implies that the base price is from the ERP module and offset by a relative amount defined by the schedule. Dynamic_percentage implies that the base price is from the ERP module and offset by a percentage defined by the schedule.

type_ticketing/types-simple:AdjustedAmou.name: AdjustedAmount
type_ticketing/types-simple:AdjustedAmou.description: The amount used to adjust admission unit price.

type_ticketing/types-simple:AdjustedDisc.name: AdjustedDiscountPct
type_ticketing/types-simple:AdjustedDisc.description: The percentage used to adjust admission unit price.

type_ticketing/types-simple:AdjustedUnit.name: AdjustedUnitPrice
type_ticketing/types-simple:AdjustedUnit.description: The calculated adjusted unit price for the admission.

type_ticketing/types-simple:AdjustedTota.name: AdjustedTotalPrice
type_ticketing/types-simple:AdjustedTota.description: The calculated adjusted total price for the admission. (Adjusted unit price \* quantity).

type_ticketing/types-simple:ArrivalFromT.name: ArrivalFromTime
type_ticketing/types-simple:ArrivalFromT.description: The earliest time a customer can arrive for the time slot.

type_ticketing/types-simple:ArrivalUntil.name: ArrivalUntilTime
type_ticketing/types-simple:ArrivalUntil.description: The latest time a customer can arrive for the time slot.

type_ticketing/types-simple:Allocatable.name: Allocatable
type_ticketing/types-simple:Allocatable.description: Indicates if the schedule is allocatable. This boolean is used to determine if the schedule can be booked and considers arrival times and capacity.

type_ticketing/types-simple:AllocationMo.name: AllocationModel
type_ticketing/types-simple:AllocationMo.description: Whether the schedule is allocated based on capacity or waiting list. When the allocation model is waiting list, the reservation requires a waiting list ID.

type_ticketing/types-simple:RemainingCap.name: RemainingCapacity
type_ticketing/types-simple:RemainingCap.description: The remaining capacity for the schedule. Note that this number can be positive even when the schedule is not allocatable.

type_ticketing/types-simple:AllocationEx.name: AllocationExplanation
type_ticketing/types-simple:AllocationEx.description: An explanation why the schedule is allocatable or not allocatable.

type_ticketing/types-simple:MemberNumber.name: MemberNumber
type_ticketing/types-simple:MemberNumber.description: The unique identifier of a member

type_ticketing/types-simple:ScannerStati.name: ScannerStation
type_ticketing/types-simple:ScannerStati.description: The name of the scanner station

type_ticketing/types-simple:CouponCode.name: CouponCode
type_ticketing/types-simple:CouponCode.description: The alias of the coupon type. This is used to identify the coupon type in the system.

type_ticketing/types-simple:CouponId.name: CouponId
type_ticketing/types-simple:CouponId.description: The unique identifier of a coupon

type_ticketing/types-simple:Admitted.name: Admitted
type_ticketing/types-simple:Admitted.description: Indicates whether the ticket has been registered as admitted to the admission

type_ticketing/types-simple:Departed.name: Departed
type_ticketing/types-simple:Departed.description: Indicates whether the ticket has been registered as departed from the admission

type_ticketing/types-simple:TicketSent.name: TicketSent
type_ticketing/types-simple:TicketSent.description: Indicates whether the ticket has been sent as an e-ticket
